The paper deals with tournament solutions, which are a concept from social choice theory and game theory. The paper also uses graph-theoretic concepts and probabilistic models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
